) %0a%3c %0a%3c Regarding its widespread use, there are not only daily posts on social media, but also social groups and music albums named after this word, which indicates that "juvenoia" is forming its own culture (4). One case triggered by "juvenoia" is heatedly discussed and published on Time(5). Moreover, multiple scientific/sociological studies researched on the "juvenoia" phenomenon and its backgrounds, trying to find evidence for the debate over this issue (6). All these scientists, sociologists, and psychologists, as well as their research, confirmed the importance of "juvenoia", which justifies the word to be officially accepted. %0a%3c %0a%3c Although I can't say for sure about the "sustainability" of this word, we still have reasons to believe in its longevity. The number one reason is that the social phenomenon associated with this word exists long before and doesn't seem to die out in the near future. Recalling back, almost every generation was concerned about something that they thought would "contaminate" the next generation. Before the Internet, it was TV; even paper books were regarded as evil centuries before. The fear and uncertainty of novel things directly lead to the fear of the new generation being less successful. However, innovation will never stop, so as this fear. %0a%3c %0a%3c Given that "juvenoia" has a meaning, is widely used, and seems to survive the time, it is reasonable to add "juvenoia" into OED. %0a%3c %0a%3c sources: %0a%3c (1) "The Internet, Youth Deviance and the Problem of Juvenoia" by David Finkelhor. video link: https://vimeo.com/16900027%0a%3c (2)wikidictionary https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/juvenoia%0a%3c (3)urban dictionary https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=juvenoia%0a%3c (4)"Juvenoia" album by Druggist https://open.spotify.com/album/2pwgL9KdnNhq6f5Hs4pesD%0a%3c (5)"What's Really Wrong With Young People Today: Juvenoia" by Chris Ferguson%0a%3c https://time.com/19818/whats-really-wrong-with-young-people-today-juvenoia/%0a%3c (6)"Juvenoia: The kids are all right, even on the Internet" by Anne Collier%0a%3c https://www.csmonitor.com/The-Culture/Family/Modern-Parenthood/2013/0723/Juvenoia-The-kids-are-all-right-even-on-the-Internet%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: FunWithWords:)%0a%3c (:Title: Juvenoia:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
